Class ModifiableTypeMap<V>

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractMap<K,​V>
java.util.TreeMap<Class<?>,​V>
nl.naturalis.common.collection.ModifiableTypeMap<V>
Type Parameters:
V - The value type
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Map<Class<?>,​V>, NavigableMap<Class<?>,​V>, SortedMap<Class<?>,​V>, TypeMap<V>
public class ModifiableTypeMap<V>
extends TreeMap<Class<?>,​V>
implements TypeMap<V>
A modifiable TypeMap implementation. Although instances of this class are modifiable, the only way to get data into them is via the constructor or via de put method. All other methods that would modify the map through an UnsupportedOperationException.
Author:
Ayco Holleman

    • ModifiableTypeMap

      public ModifiableTypeMap​(Map<Class<?>,​V> source, List<Predicate<Class<?>>> sortOptions)
      Creates a new TypeMap from the entries in the specified source map. The source map's entries are first copied and sorted such that the lowest-level classes enter this Map first while base classes and interfaces come last. The sortOptions argument allows you to apply extra sorting to the map keys beyond the sorting imposed by an internally created Comparator. The predicates are passed on to the Comparator such that if the Predicate evaluates to true for the first argument to Comparator.compare(class1, class2, and false for the second argument, then class1 will be pushed to the front and class2 to the back.
      Parameters:
      source -
      sortOptions -
